## Flow-3: Agent Turn Execution

**Modules involved**: agent-config, provider, runtime, relay
**Entry**: `AgentInstance::turn()` called with system prompt + context
**Exit**: `TurnResult` returned with response + tool calls + handoff document

### Overview

A single Agent Turn is the atomic unit of agent work. It takes a scoped context (system prompt + relevant specs + handoff history), streams through the LLM, executes any tool calls, and produces a structured result.

### Sequence Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant PipelineEngine
    participant AgentInstance
    participant Profession
    participant Soul
    participant ClaudeProvider
    participant ContextManager
    participant ToolRegistry

    PipelineEngine->>AgentInstance: spawn(profession_config)
    AgentInstance->>Profession: resolve config
    AgentInstance->>Soul: render_system_prompt()
    AgentInstance->>ContextManager: compile_context(scoped_specs)
    AgentInstance->>ClaudeProvider: chat_stream(system_prompt, context, tools)

    loop Tool call loop
        ClaudeProvider-->>AgentInstance: tool_call request
        AgentInstance->>ToolRegistry: execute_with_permission(tool, input)
        ToolRegistry-->>AgentInstance: result
        AgentInstance->>ClaudeProvider: submit tool_result
    end

    ClaudeProvider-->>AgentInstance: final text + stop_reason
    AgentInstance->>AgentInstance: generate_handoff_document()
    AgentInstance-->>PipelineEngine: TurnResult { text, tool_calls, handoff, tokens }
```

### Key Steps

#### Step 1: Agent Spawning
**Trigger**: `PipelineEngine` requests an agent for a step
**Processing**: `AgentInstance` resolves profession (tools, sections, constraints) + soul (personality) + model (provider/tier)
**Data Flow**: profession config ‚Üí `AgentInstance` + `Soul` + `ModelConfig`

#### Step 2: System Prompt Rendering
**Trigger**: Agent instance ready
**Processing**: Compose system prompt from: soul markdown + profession instructions + owned sections + allowed tools list + skill definitions + constraints
**Data Flow**: `Soul` + `Profession` + `Skills` ‚Üí system prompt string

#### Step 3: Context Compilation
**Trigger**: System prompt rendered
**Processing**: `ContextManager` loads relevant specs (owned + readable sections), compacts if token budget exceeded
**Data Flow**: `SpecsStore` ‚Üí `ContextManager` ‚Üí compacted context messages

#### Step 4: LLM Streaming
**Trigger**: Context ready
**Processing**: `ClaudeProvider.chat_stream()` sends request to Anthropic/OpenAI/Ollama, parses SSE stream
**Data Flow**: system prompt + context ‚Üí API request ‚Üí SSE stream ‚Üí `StreamEvent` parsing

#### Step 5: Tool Execution
**Trigger**: LLM requests tool call
**Processing**: `ToolRegistry.execute()` checks permission policy (`Allow`/`Ask`/`ReadOnly`), runs tool, returns result
**Data Flow**: tool request ‚Üí permission check ‚Üí execution ‚Üí result ‚Üí back to LLM

#### Step 6: Handoff Generation
**Trigger**: LLM turn completes (stop reason = end_turn)
**Processing**: Extract structured fields: decisions, work products, spec updates, open questions, token usage
**Data Flow**: turn result ‚Üí `HandoffDocument` ‚Üí `PipelineEngine`

### Related Specs
- `AgentConfig-A1` ‚Äî Agent Instance Lifecycle
- `AgentConfig-D1` ‚Äî `AgentInstance` / `SoulConfig` / `ModelConfig` structs
- `Provider-A1` ‚Äî Unified provider architecture
- `Relay-D2` ‚Äî HandoffDocument generation
- `Runtime-D1` ‚Äî `PermissionPolicy` and `ContextManager`

