## Flow-4: Spec Document Lifecycle

**Modules involved**: specs, forge (agent tools)
**Entry**: Agent reads or writes a spec via `read_specs` / `update_spec`
**Exit**: Spec persisted to `.ad` file with derived statuses and relations

### Overview

Specs are the single source of truth in AutoForge. They follow a strict pyramid (Goals ‚Üí Architecture ‚Üí Designs ‚Üí Plans ‚Üí Tests ‚Üí Reviews ‚Üí Reports) and are maintained by profession-specific agents through structured tools.

### Sequence Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Architect
    participant read_specs
    participant update_spec
    participant SpecsStore
    participant parse_ad_file
    participant derive_statuses
    participant rebuild_relations
    participant Disk

    Architect->>read_specs: read_specs(project="auto-forge", section="architecture")
    read_specs->>SpecsStore: load_module_format()
    SpecsStore->>Disk: read *.ad files
    SpecsStore->>parse_ad_file: parse markdown ‚Üí SpecItems
    parse_ad_file-->>SpecsStore: structured items
    SpecsStore-->>read_specs: return items
    read_specs-->>Architect: architecture specs

    Architect->>update_spec: update_spec(section="architecture", item_id="A99", ...)
    update_spec->>SpecsStore: upsert item
    SpecsStore->>derive_statuses: auto-update Goal statuses
    SpecsStore->>rebuild_relations: scan depends_on / related
    SpecsStore->>Disk: save_module_format()
    Disk-->>SpecsStore: *.ad files written
    SpecsStore-->>update_spec: success
    update_spec-->>Architect: confirmation
```

### Key Steps

#### Step 1: Loading
**Trigger**: `read_specs` tool called
**Processing**: `SpecsStore` reads module-format `.ad` files, parses markdown into `SpecItem` structs with metadata
**Data Flow**: Disk ‚Üí `parse_ad_file()` ‚Üí `SpecItem` list ‚Üí agent context

#### Step 2: Editing
**Trigger**: `update_spec` tool called
**Processing**: `SpecsStore` upserts the item; if item ID has module prefix, routes to correct module directory
**Data Flow**: agent ‚Üí `update_spec` ‚Üí `SpecsStore` ‚Üí module directory

#### Step 3: Status Derivation
**Trigger**: After spec update
**Processing**: `derive_statuses()` auto-updates Goal statuses based on related Plans/Tests/Reviews progress
**Data Flow**: spec changes ‚Üí `derive_statuses()` ‚Üí updated statuses

#### Step 4: Relation Rebuild
**Trigger**: After status derivation
**Processing**: `rebuild_relations()` scans `depends_on` fields and content text to build bidirectional `related` links
**Data Flow**: all items ‚Üí `rebuild_relations()` ‚Üí relation graph

#### Step 5: Persistence
**Trigger**: After relation rebuild
**Processing**: `save_module_format()` writes each module's specs back to its `.ad` files
**Data Flow**: `SpecItem` list ‚Üí `serialize_section_to_ad()` ‚Üí Disk

### Related Specs
- `Specs-G1` ‚Äî Spec pyramid taxonomy
- `Specs-G2` ‚Äî Bidirectional traceability
- `Specs-A1` ‚Äî Goals Hierarchy Architecture
- `Specs-D1` ‚Äî Category renderer polymorphism
- `Specs-D8` ‚Äî Architect-maintained `overview.ad`

